<@U0546QERR>: before you worry about overdraw first figure out if your performance is actually suffering from that/nested views. That being said, its really easy to end up with unnecessary nested view groups and bad overdraw just from attempting to satisfy background/border requirements. Something i’ve done to get rid of that is use a single relative layout and place my views where they should be, then create a custom drawable that paints all your background/border nonsense underneath.

initial_comment.comment: Learning about Gradle. Could anyone explain to me why there are two places where these repos are defined? Why would one in buildscript closure and the other outside?

text: <@U0F5VSCNA>: one sets the repositories for the buildscript dependencies, and the other your project dependencies
buildscript dependencies typically being your plugins
<@U053LEHJN>: makes sense – but how come there is a `repositories` defined outside of buildscript? Shouldn’t all of my repo dependancies be defined in `dependancies`?
<@U0F5VSCNA>: Like I said, the `repositories` closure outside the `buildscript` block sets the repositories for the current project
I have many dependancies that don’t have anything defined in repositories – that’s the confusing part
everything inside `buildscript` runs before the rest of your gradle scripts
how come some dependancies (if not most) do not have to have a statement in repositories?
lots of libs are hosted on jcenter or mavenCentral
so your entry there should cover most stuff
from your script up there it looks like fabric uses its own maven repo so that's why you have to tell gradle about it separately

file.name: Untitled.groovy
file.title: Untitled
file.preview_highlight:
dependencies {
	compile 'com.squareup.retrofit:retrofit:1.9.0'
	compile 'com.squareup.okhttp:okhttp:2.5.0’
}

text: So these ones … would be defined on maven or jcenter? How does the gradle file know where to look?
it checks your repositories in order
i always have jcenter() first so i don't spam jitpack or something with requests for libs it doesn't have
